.XP
\(bu
The Makefile is turned into pair-wise ordered dependencies.
.br
.ps 16
.vs 17
.sp 0.5
.TS
tab(;);
lf(CW) l.
prog: a.o b.o;prog \(<- a.o
    cc a.o b.o -o prog;prog \(<- b.o
.sp 0.5
a.o: a.c a.h;a.o \(<- a.c
    cc -c a.c;a.o \(<- a.h
.sp 0.5
b.o: b.c a.h;b.o \(<- b.c
    cc -c b.c;b.o \(<- a.h
.sp 0.5
a.c a.h: a.y;a.c \(<- a.y
    yacc -d a.y;a.h \(<- a.y
    \fImv \&...\fI
.TE
.XP
\(bu
The pairs are then shuffled to find a valid ordering.
.bp
